      <em>Director of Operations</em>
    </p>
    <p>Arwyn has worked for social change throughout her career.  She started by working with legislators in the NH State House and then for 5 years as a fundraiser for political campaigns all across the country.  She left the world of politics when hearing about the atrocity of human trafficking in the modern world and worked with Love146, a group out of Connecticut that works to fight child sex trafficking, as their Director of Development for a year.</p>
    <p>She returned to the Greater Boston Area in 2007 and remained involved in the issue as a member of task forces and as a speaker on modern-day slavery while working in the Development Division of the Museum of Science.  She brings an understanding of grassroots organizing, social marketing and non-profit organization through her varied career as a fundraiser.</p>
